org.divxdede.text.formatter

Class PatternFormatter.Flags

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.divxdede.text.formatter.PatternFormatter.Flags
  • Enclosing class:
    PatternFormatter

    public static class PatternFormatter.Flags
extends Object
    Represent flags set usable for an ArgumentDetails This class is compatible with the java.util.Formatter$Flags class in bit values and can be used with java.util.Formattable objects

    Flags can't be instanciate directly. To create a flags set, you have two way:

    • Parse one from their characters with Flags.parse(String s)
    • Compose a flags set from standard ones with Flags.and(Flags)
       Flags flagsA = Flags.parse("+,");
   Flags flagsB = Flags.PLUS.and( Flags.GROUP );
